  "prompt": "Are there any other straight men diagnosed with histrionic personality disorder?",
  "response": "Yes, histrionic personality disorder (HPD) can affect individuals of any gender or sexual orientation. While historically HPD has been more frequently diagnosed in women, men can also be diagnosed with the disorder, regardless of their sexual orientation. HPD is characterized by patterns of excessive emotionality and attention-seeking behavior. If you are seeking information about specific individuals or cases, that information might not be publicly available due to privacy concerns. However, the diagnosis is not exclusive to any particular gender or sexual orientation.",
